Therefore, cs.PR (Probability), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions an extension argument similar to Kirszbraun's theorem, which is a result in computational geometry, suggesting that cs.CC (Computational Geometry) may also be a relevant sub-category.
